Package: ScreenR
Type: Package
Title: Package to Perform High Throughput Biological Screening
Version: 0.99.41
Date: 2022-04-01 
Authors@R: c(person("Emanuel Michele", "Soda", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  email = "emanuelsoda@gmail.com", 
                  comment = c(ORICD = "0000-0002-2301-6465")),
             person("Elena", "Ceccacci", role = c("aut"),
                   email = "elena.ceccacci@ieo.it", 
                   comment = c(ORICD = "0000-0002-2285-8994")))
Description: ScreenR is an easy and effective package to perform hits 
             identification in loss of function High Throughput Biological 
             Screening performed with shRNAs library. ScreenR combines the 
             power of softwares like edgeR with the semplicity of the Tydiverse 
             metapackage. ScreenR executes a pipeline able to find candidate 
             hits from barcode counts data and integrates a wide range of 
             visualization for each step of the analysis.
